%S A394970 1,1,1,0,1,0,2,0,64,0,1374132,0
%N A394970 Number of isotopism classes of row-Hamiltonian Latin squares of order n.
%C A394970 A Latin square is row-Hamiltonian if the permutation mapping row i to row j consists of a single cycle, for all distinct i,j. An isotopism class contains all the Latin squares obtainable by permuting rows, permuting columns and permuting symbols.
%C A394970 a(n) = 0 if n > 2 is even [Wanless].
%D A394970 J. Allsop and I.M. Wanless, Perfect 1-factorisations of K_{11,11}, Australasian J. Combinatorics 95 (2026), 114-130.
%e A394970 The Cayley table of any cyclic group of prime order is a row-Hamiltonian Latin square.
%Y A394970 Cf. A394971, A120489.
%K A394970 nonn,more,new
%O A394970 1,7
%A A394970 _Ian Wanless_, Apr 08 2026
